                      <span>10</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-01-06</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>When i received Keri Smith's book in the mail i literally jumped for joy! I made a bowl of lentil soup and proceeded to devour "Living out Loud" while devouring my soup. Instantly i knew that Keri's book would become comfort food for my creative soul.<BR> <BR>In the tradition of Sark, who inspires us creatively, Living out Loud does the same only Keri's adorable coilbound book departs from Sark by supplying the reader with tear out postcards, cut-out shrines, stickers and juicy tear out Permission cards (this really appealed to the child in me!). For those of us who have the patience of a gnat, you will enjoy the brief topics that are beautifully illustrated. I have been an artist for over 30 years and feel that i have found a kindred spirit in Keri Smith and so will you!! <P>This book is sure to become my pocket Muse to be used again and again for inspiration and great project ideas. I highly recommend it!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">My breakfast companion</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
